column2: The dashboard has a visually appealing design
column4: I would find the information presented by the product useful if I was traveling by air.
column5: The layout of the dashboard helps me quickly find what I need.
column6: It is easy to understand the meaning of the data visualizations used.
column7: Interactive elements (e.g., filters, dropdowns, clickable charts) are intuitive and responsive.
column8: The dashboard clearly presents the most important information at a glance
column9: I would recommend this dashboard to others.
column10: Are you involved in the airline industry?
column11: Do you have any suggestions or feedback?
Data is neatly presented and can quickly under the outputs
Delay risk model is not very responsive to destination inputs and other interactive tools
Further explanation of the axis’ of the graphs.  For example on breakdown for causes the vertical axis says “value” but what is the actual value?
Make the drop downs stand out, and darker backgrounds can make the info pop more
Full names of Airport codes could maybe be shown. What is “nas delays”?
Be able to compare between airlines as not all airlines are consistent with scheduled flights.

I think the most important thing to me if I was a traveler using this application would be why my flight is delayed and predicted probably of delays. So that information should be near the top for me.
